Planigle is a Ruby on Rails based agile planning application.

Required Components - License:
Ruby - GPLv2 (http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/downloads/)
Rails - MIT (http://www.rubyonrails.com/down)
MySQL - GPLv2 (http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/5.0.html)
HTTP Server - Apache (http://httpd.apache.org/download.cgi)

Embedded Components - License:
Restful Authentication (Rails Plugin) - MIT
ActiveScaffold (Rails Plugin) - MIT

Suggested Gems:
mysql

Suggested Eclipse plug-ins:
Aptana (http://update.aptana.com/update/3.2/)
  Note: This currently doesn't work with versions of RubyGems later than 0.9.4.
Subversion (http://subclipse.tigris.org/update_1.2.x)
Flex (See http://www.adobe.com/cfusion/tdrc/index.cfm?product=flex_eclipse&loc=en_us)
  Note: There is a 60 day free trial, but this costs money if you chose to use it
SQL Explorer (http://eclipsesql.sourceforge.net/)
  Note: You can get the MySQL JDBC driver from http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/5.0.html

Additional Guidance:
By default, the html application assumes that SSL is available (it was tested by providing this via Apache).
To make it HTTP only (no HTTPS), change Application>>secure_protocol to return 'http'.